{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":285,"text":"This is an image of the planet Earth."},{"time":3178,"text":"It looks very much like the Apollo pictures"},{"time":6271,"text":"that are very well known."},{"time":7882,"text":"There is something different;"},{"time":9952,"text":"you can click on it,"},{"time":11399,"text":"and if you click on it,"},{"time":12597,"text":"you can zoom in on almost any place on the Earth."},{"time":15669,"text":"For instance, this is a bird's-eye view"},{"time":17668,"text":"of the EPFL campus."},{"time":20334,"text":"In many cases, you can also see"},{"time":22442,"text":"how a building looks from a nearby street."},{"time":26182,"text":"This is pretty amazing."},{"time":27604,"text":"But there's something missing in this wonderful tour:"},{"time":31031,"text":"It's time."},{"time":33219,"text":"i'm not really sure when this picture was taken."},{"time":36289,"text":"I'm not even sure it was taken"},{"time":37701,"text":"at the same moment as the bird's-eye view."},{"time":43784,"text":"In my lab, we develop tools"},{"time":45993,"text":"to travel not only in space"},{"time":47757,"text":"but also through time."},{"time":50315,"text":"The kind of question we're asking is"},{"time":52185,"text":"Is it possible to build something"},{"time":53578,"text":"like Google Maps of the past?"},{"time":55756,"text":"Can I add a slider on top of Google Maps"},{"time":59066,"text":"and just change the year,"},{"time":60869,"text":"seeing how it was 100 years before,"},{"time":62660,"text":"1,000 years before?"},{"time":64329,"text":"Is that possible?"},{"time":66452,"text":"Can I reconstruct social networks of the past?"},{"time":68704,"text":"Can I make a Facebook of the Middle Ages?"},{"time":71753,"text":"So, can I build time machines?"},{"time":75529,"text":"Maybe we can just say, \"No, it's not possible.\""},{"time":78094,"text":"Or, maybe, we can think of it from an information point of view."},{"time":81904,"text":"This is what I call the information mushroom."},{"time":85094,"text":"Vertically, you have the time."},{"time":86677,"text":"and horizontally, the amount of digital information available."},{"time":89417,"text":"Obviously, in the last 10 years, we have much information."},{"time":92899,"text":"And obviously the more we go in the past, the less information we have."},{"time":96447,"text":"If we want to build something like Google Maps of the past,"},{"time":98765,"text":"or Facebook of the past,"},{"time":100259,"text":"we need to enlarge this space,"},{"time":101833,"text":"we need to make that like a rectangle."},{"time":103771,"text":"How do we do that?"},{"time":105281,"text":"One way is digitization."},{"time":107395,"text":"There's a lot of material available --"},{"time":109190,"text":"newspaper, printed books, thousands of printed books."},{"time":115460,"text":"I can digitize all these."},{"time":117228,"text":"I can extract information from these."},{"time":119965,"text":"Of course, the more you go in the past,\nthe less information you will have."},{"time":123508,"text":"So, it might not be enough."},{"time":126154,"text":"So, I can do what historians do."},{"time":128562,"text":"I can extrapolate."},{"time":130086,"text":"This is what we call, in computer science, simulation."},{"time":134556,"text":"If I take a log book,"},{"time":136307,"text":"I can consider, it's not just a log book"},{"time":138711,"text":"of a Venetian captain going to a particular journey."},{"time":141683,"text":"I can consider it is actually a log book"},{"time":143326,"text":"which is representative of\nmany journeys of that period."},{"time":145908,"text":"I'm extrapolating."},{"time":148153,"text":"If I have a painting of a facade,"},{"time":150191,"text":"I can consider it's not just that particular building,"},{"time":152942,"text":"but probably it also shares the same grammar"},{"time":156874,"text":"of buildings where we lost any information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160915,"text":"So if we want to construct a time machine,"},{"time":163773,"text":"we need two things."},{"time":165112,"text":"We need very large archives,"},{"time":167346,"text":"and we need excellent specialists."},{"time":170088,"text":"The Venice Time Machine,"},{"time":171962,"text":"the project I'm going to talk to you about,"},{"time":173767,"text":"is a joint project between the EPFL"},{"time":176787,"text":"and the University of Venice Ca'Foscari."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179765,"text":"There's something very peculiar about Venice,"},{"time":181930,"text":"that its administration has been"},{"time":184604,"text":"very, very bureaucratic."},{"time":186798,"text":"They've been keeping track of everything,"},{"time":188991,"text":"almost like Google today."},{"time":191906,"text":"At the Archivio di Stato,"},{"time":193420,"text":"you have 80 kilometers of archives"},{"time":195184,"text":"documenting every aspect"},{"time":197193,"text":"of the life of Venice over\nmore than 1,000 years."},{"time":199439,"text":"You have every boat that goes out,"},{"time":201359,"text":"every boat that comes in."},{"time":202435,"text":"You have every change that was made in the city."},{"time":205232,"text":"This is all there."},{"time":208523,"text":"We are setting up a 10-year digitization program"},{"time":212431,"text":"which has the objective of transforming"},{"time":214108,"text":"this immense archive"},{"time":215492,"text":"into a giant information system."},{"time":217918,"text":"The type of objective we want to reach"},{"time":219775,"text":"is 450 books a day that can be digitized."},{"time":224501,"text":"Of course, when you digitize, that's not enough,"},{"time":226748,"text":"because these documents,"},{"time":228035,"text":"most of them are in Latin, in Tuscan,"},{"time":230689,"text":"in Venetian dialect,"},{"time":232204,"text":"so you need to transcribe them,"},{"time":233879,"text":"to translate them in some cases,"},{"time":235560,"text":"to index them,"},{"time":236680,"text":"and this is obviously not easy."},{"time":238844,"text":"In particular, traditional optical\ncharacter recognition method"},{"time":242688,"text":"that can be used for printed manuscripts,"},{"time":244112,"text":"they do not work well on the handwritten document."},{"time":248116,"text":"So the solution is actually to take inspiration"},{"time":250246,"text":"from another domain: speech recognition."},{"time":253147,"text":"This is a domain of something \nthat seems impossible,"},{"time":255202,"text":"which can actually be done,"},{"time":257739,"text":"simply by putting additional constraints."},{"time":259933,"text":"If you have a very good model"},{"time":261519,"text":"of a language which is used,"},{"time":263045,"text":"if you have a very good model of a document,"},{"time":265131,"text":"how well they are structured."},{"time":266563,"text":"And these are administrative documents."},{"time":267931,"text":"They are well structured in many cases."},{"time":270063,"text":"If you divide this huge archive into smaller subsets"},{"time":273371,"text":"where a smaller subset\nactually shares similar features,"},{"time":276248,"text":"then there's a chance of success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282761,"text":"If we reach that stage, then there's something else:"},{"time":285196,"text":"we can extract from this document events."},{"time":288718,"text":"Actually probably 10 billion events"},{"time":291016,"text":"can be extracted from this archive."},{"time":292947,"text":"And this giant information system"},{"time":294671,"text":"can be searched in many ways."},{"time":296487,"text":"You can ask questions like,"},{"time":297855,"text":"\"Who lived in this palazzo in 1323?\""},{"time":300615,"text":"\"How much cost a sea bream at the Realto market"},{"time":302837,"text":"in 1434?\""},{"time":304561,"text":"\"What was the salary"},{"time":306021,"text":"of a glass maker in Murano"},{"time":308066,"text":"maybe over a decade?\""},{"time":309472,"text":"You can ask even bigger questions"},{"time":310894,"text":"because it will be semantically coded."},{"time":313632,"text":"And then what you can do is put that in space,"},{"time":315772,"text":"because much of this information is spatial."},{"time":317945,"text":"And from that, you can do things like"},{"time":319880,"text":"reconstructing this extraordinary journey"},{"time":321993,"text":"of that city that managed to\nhave a sustainable development"},{"time":325349,"text":"over a thousand years,"},{"time":327475,"text":"managing to have all the time"},{"time":329095,"text":"a form of equilibrium with its environment."},{"time":331956,"text":"You can reconstruct that journey,"},{"time":333204,"text":"visualize it in many different ways."},{"time":336100,"text":"But of course, you cannot understand \nVenice if you just look at the city."},{"time":338799,"text":"You have to put it in a larger European context."},{"time":341195,"text":"So the idea is also to document all the things"},{"time":344016,"text":"that worked at the European level."},{"time":346439,"text":"We can reconstruct also the journey"},{"time":348403,"text":"of the Venetian maritime empire,"},{"time":350393,"text":"how it progressively controlled the Adriatic Sea,"},{"time":353559,"text":"how it became the most powerful medieval empire"},{"time":357305,"text":"of its time,"},{"time":358866,"text":"controlling most of the sea routes"},{"time":361038,"text":"from the east to the south."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365305,"text":"But you can even do other things,"},{"time":367621,"text":"because in these maritime routes,"},{"time":369898,"text":"there are regular patterns."},{"time":371889,"text":"You can go one step beyond"},{"time":374382,"text":"and actually create a simulation system,"},{"time":376502,"text":"create a Mediterranean simulator"},{"time":379317,"text":"which is capable actually of reconstructing"},{"time":381910,"text":"even the information we are missing,"},{"time":384112,"text":"which would enable us to have \nquestions you could ask"},{"time":387100,"text":"like if you were using a route planner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390088,"text":"\"If I am in Corfu in June 1323"},{"time":393159,"text":"and want to go to Constantinople,"},{"time":395685,"text":"where can I take a boat?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":397828,"text":"Probably we can answer this question"},{"time":399195,"text":"with one or two or three days' precision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403668,"text":"\"How much will it cost?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":405275,"text":"\"What are the chance of encountering pirates?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":408867,"text":"Of course, you understand,"},{"time":410678,"text":"the central scientific challenge\nof a project like this one"},{"time":413287,"text":"is qualifying, quantifying and representing"},{"time":417016,"text":"uncertainty and inconsistency\nat each step of this process."},{"time":420346,"text":"There are errors everywhere,"},{"time":423058,"text":"errors in the document, it's\nthe wrong name of the captain,"},{"time":425547,"text":"some of the boats never actually took to sea."},{"time":428760,"text":"There are errors in translation, interpretative biases,"},{"time":433624,"text":"and on top of that, if you add algorithmic processes,"},{"time":437090,"text":"you're going to have errors in recognition,"},{"time":440039,"text":"errors in extraction,"},{"time":442000,"text":"so you have very, very uncertain data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446481,"text":"So how can we detect and\ncorrect these inconsistencies?"},{"time":450238,"text":"How can we represent that form of uncertainty?"},{"time":453898,"text":"It's difficult. One thing you can do"},{"time":455995,"text":"is document each step of the process,"},{"time":458221,"text":"not only coding the historical information"},{"time":460669,"text":"but what we call the meta-historical information,"},{"time":463348,"text":"how is historical knowledge constructed,"},{"time":466011,"text":"documenting each step."},{"time":468009,"text":"That will not guarantee that we actually converge"},{"time":469654,"text":"toward a single story of Venice,"},{"time":472104,"text":"but probably we can actually reconstruct"},{"time":474242,"text":"a fully documented potential story of Venice."},{"time":477290,"text":"Maybe there's not a single map."},{"time":478749,"text":"Maybe there are several maps."},{"time":480869,"text":"The system should allow for that,"},{"time":483085,"text":"because we have to deal with\na new form of uncertainty,"},{"time":485944,"text":"which is really new for this type of giant databases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490585,"text":"And how should we communicate"},{"time":492790,"text":"this new research to a large audience?"},{"time":496769,"text":"Again, Venice is extraordinary for that."},{"time":499432,"text":"With the millions of visitors that come every year,"},{"time":501603,"text":"it's actually one of the best places"},{"time":503366,"text":"to try to invent the museum of the future."},{"time":506354,"text":"Imagine, horizontally you see the reconstructed map"},{"time":509658,"text":"of a given year,"},{"time":510944,"text":"and vertically, you see the document"},{"time":513902,"text":"that served the reconstruction,"},{"time":515413,"text":"paintings, for instance."},{"time":518813,"text":"Imagine an immersive system that permits"},{"time":521393,"text":"to go and dive and reconstruct\nthe Venice of a given year,"},{"time":524895,"text":"some experience you could share within a group."},{"time":527610,"text":"On the contrary, imagine actually that you start"},{"time":529856,"text":"from a document, a Venetian manuscript,"},{"time":532063,"text":"and you show, actually, what\nyou can construct out of it,"},{"time":535112,"text":"how it is decoded,"},{"time":536884,"text":"how the context of that document can be recreated."},{"time":539299,"text":"This is an image from an exhibit"},{"time":541184,"text":"which is currently conducted in Geneva"},{"time":543460,"text":"with that type of system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545814,"text":"So to conclude, we can say that"},{"time":547989,"text":"research in the humanities is about to undergo"},{"time":551068,"text":"an evolution which is maybe similar"},{"time":552870,"text":"to what happened to life sciences 30 years ago."},{"time":557452,"text":"It's really a question of scale."},{"time":562130,"text":"We see projects which are"},{"time":565433,"text":"much beyond any single research team can do,"},{"time":569276,"text":"and this is really new for the humanities,"},{"time":571519,"text":"which very often take the habit of working"},{"time":575388,"text":"in small groups or only with a couple of researchers."},{"time":579396,"text":"When you visit the Archivio di Stato,"},{"time":581514,"text":"you feel this is beyond what any single team can do,"},{"time":584336,"text":"and that should be a joint and common effort."},{"time":588170,"text":"So what we must do for this paradigm shift"},{"time":591276,"text":"is actually foster a new generation"},{"time":593178,"text":"of \"digital humanists\""},{"time":594715,"text":"that are going to be ready for this shift."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596805,"text":"I thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598764,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}